<i>Believe me, it works</i>
<i>Oh, yes, it does</i>

35:20.351 --> 35:23.252
Are you gonna be here
in the morning, Daddy?

35:24.222 --> 35:26.918
- I'm afraid not.
- Why?

35:26.991 --> 35:31.792
- Mommy won't let you stay?
- No, it's not Mommy.

35:31.863 --> 35:34.559
Your mom is
the best mom in the world, okay?

35:34.632 --> 35:37.658
Don't ever forget that. It's just...

35:39.971 --> 35:41.734
Daddy's on a time-out right now.

35:44.976 --> 35:47.308
Are you ever coming home, Daddy?

35:50.047 --> 35:53.983
- I hope so.
- I hope so, too.

35:58.055 --> 36:00.751
<i>So I can sin with you</i>

36:00.825 --> 36:03.157
<i>She holds a key</i>

36:03.227 --> 36:05.525
<i>Tight in her hand</i>

36:05.596 --> 36:07.587
<i>Clutching his neck</i>

36:07.999 --> 36:09.728
Rachel, we're home!

36:10.234 --> 36:12.725
<i>Listen, you sinner</i>

36:12.803 --> 36:14.065
<i>I'm sinning, too</i>

36:14.138 --> 36:17.835
She's gone. You tried, Brooke.

36:17.909 --> 36:20.139
I guess she just wasn't ready.

36:20.344 --> 36:22.244
<i>She holds a key</i>

36:22.313 --> 36:24.611
<i>Tight in her hand</i>

36:24.715 --> 36:27.411
<i>Clutching his neck</i>

36:27.485 --> 36:29.385
<i>Listen, everybody</i>

36:29.453 --> 36:31.546
<i>She holds a key</i>

36:32.023 --> 36:36.585
So we didn't get to talk much tonight.
What's your story?

36:39.030 --> 36:42.158
I just got out of jail for killing my brother.

36:42.233 --> 36:45.259
Right. So did you do it?

36:48.439 --> 36:49.531
Yeah.

36:59.784 --> 37:02.082
I saw the light on.
I wanted to make sure that

37:02.153 --> 37:04.644
Rachel wasn't cleaning us out.

37:04.722 --> 37:08.283
What is that supposed to mean?
Have you been to my house?

37:10.294 --> 37:14.526
- Did you say something to her?
- Nothing the mirror couldn't have told her.

37:14.599 --> 37:16.590
Leave my friends alone, okay?

37:16.667 --> 37:19.192
I was trying to protect you
from making another mistake.

37:19.270 --> 37:23.070
- Firing Rachel was a mistake.
- That was business.

37:23.140 --> 37:26.507
That is not the way
I want my business to be.

37:26.577 --> 37:29.171
- People deserve better. She...
- You see?

37:29.247 --> 37:32.614
This is exactly why you weren't
included in the meeting today.

37:32.683 --> 37:36.585
You're too emotional. You need to
remove emotion from business.

37:37.888 --> 37:42.621
- That's why I'm here.
- Now. You're here now.

37:44.662 --> 37:47.722
What about all of those years
I was growing up?

37:49.533 --> 37:54.402
You never wanted to be a part of my life
until I started this company.

37:54.472 --> 37:55.769
What?

37:55.840 --> 37:59.105
Cheerleading, school president...

38:00.911 --> 38:04.574
Stop being childish.
You're the face of a company,

38:04.649 --> 38:08.949
and you took your company as
far as you could on your own.

38:09.020 --> 38:11.511
Then you came to me
when you needed help.

38:11.589 --> 38:15.958
Well, Rachel needed my help,
and you made me fire her.

38:16.027 --> 38:20.396
You earned my help, Brooke.
Rachel didn't earn yours.

38:20.464 --> 38:21.863
I earned it?

38:23.334 --> 38:28.931
A daughter is not supposed to have
to earn her mother's help or her love.

38:29.006 --> 38:31.497
It is supposed to be unconditional.

38:33.044 --> 38:34.306
Whatever.

38:37.682 --> 38:39.149
You're fired.

38:44.789 --> 38:46.654
What did you just say?

38:47.992 --> 38:50.586
I said,

38:50.661 --> 38:52.856
you are fired.

38:54.198 --> 38:58.294
You're going to fire me
and risk our entire company?

38:58.402 --> 39:03.601
But it's not our company.
It's my company. Remember?

39:04.608 --> 39:07.099
I am not an employee.

39:12.950 --> 39:14.577
I am your mother.

39:15.453 --> 39:16.681
I know.

39:18.656 --> 39:19.816
You're fired.

39:26.063 --> 39:27.587
You can go now.

